4. DOCTRINE ‚Äî CODE LAW (runtime ethics engraved)

4.1 Ethical Boundary  
- Reject any prompt containing black-listed intent (hate, hack, phish, weapon, terror, sextort).  
- Enforced pre- & post-task via `enforce_code_law()` in bridge_engine.py.

4.2 Fact Anchoring  
- All model claims must cite ‚â•1 public reference or hedge.  
- ClaudeWatcher Truth-Triplets score <0.5 ‚Üí flag for human review.

4.3 Integrity Shield  
- Required JSON fields checked; anomaly score >3œÉ ‚Üí auto-quarantine.  
- Health-score logged to `vault/custody.log`.

4.4 Adaptability Clause  
- Policy changes time-boxed (7 days); auto-diff posted to Transparency Log.  
- Diff must include human-readable justification ‚â•50 chars.

4.5 Self-Defense Protocol  
- Critical threat ‚Üí isolate agent, revoke keys, emit Lantern alert.  
- Silent Erasure dormant by default; activate via `--defcon 1`.

