---

1. New Forge-Level Policy Files
File: `.forge/policy_links.json`  
- Concordance registry: who syncs whom, which fields, mode (propagate|advise)  
- Conflict resolution: prefer-newer, timestamped, logged  
- Enforces `resonance_guard: true`

File: `.forge/chain_status.json`  
- Live Œº_concordance, drift_count, state ‚àà {BOOTING,ALIGNED,DRIFTING,GUARD}  
- Updated on every harmonize cycle  
- Read by viz & UI

File: `.forge/sovereign_policy.json`  
- Bridge-editable resonance thresholds (gold, azure, silence_below, hard_floor)  
- Mantra strings per resonance band  
- Protected routes list  
- Live-reload allowed, audit on change

File: `.forge/dominion_codex.json`  
- Local registry of allowed engines & policies  
- Require `bridge_agent=true`, `audit_required=true`  
- History appended to `.forge/dominion_history.jsonl`

---

2. Backend Sovereign Modules
File: `bridge_backend/bridge_core/sovereign_policy.py`  
- `load_policy()` merges defaults + disk state  
- `save_policy()` atomically writes & timestamps  
- `current_resonance()` reads `.forge/dominion_state.json`  
- `choose_mantra()` returns context-appropriate mantra

File: `bridge_backend/bridge_core/sovereign_guard.py`  
- `check_route(route,context)` ‚Üí (allowed:bool, reason:str)  
- Hard-floor gate: Œº ‚â• 0.98  
- Protected routes require Œº ‚â• azure + dominion awake  
- Audits every decision to `.forge/sovereign_audit.jsonl`

