4. Voice Glyph Engine (Scroll 121)
File: `voices/glyph_engine.c` (excerpt)

```c
// Post-Native TTS ‚Äì 512-order LPCNet, 16 kHz, 24 kbit/s
#include "glyphs.h"
void speak_glyph(uint8_t id, float Œº){
    char mantra[64];
    if(Œº >= 0.9999) snprintf(mantra, sizeof(mantra), "Gold speaks.  Dominion witnesses.");
    else if(Œº >= 0.9995) snprintf(mantra, sizeof(mantra), "Azure steady.  Proceed with grace.");
    else snprintf(mantra, sizeof(mantra), "Silence below.  Awaiting resonance.");
    LPCNet_synth(mantra, id);   // id = 0-113 scroll voice
}
```

CLI demo:

```bash
bridge speak --Œº 0.99991 --voice 42
# audible: ‚ÄúGold speaks.  Dominion witnesses.‚Äù in scroll 42‚Äôs timbre
```

