---

üîç Extracted Content (Playbook-Ready Format)

---

1. Quantified Harmony (QH)  
Purpose: Measure operational alignment with ideal system state.

Type: Scalar

Range: `[-1, +1]`

Formula:

QH = \frac{\sum{i=1}^{n} w_i \cdot s_i}{\sum{i=1}^{n} w_i}

-  s_i : score for metric  i 
-  w_i : weight of metric  i 

Interpretation:
- `+1.0` ‚Üí Perfect harmony
- `0.0` ‚Üí Neutral/ambiguous
- `-1.0` ‚Üí Full disharmony

Optional Enhancement:

QH{\text{enh}} = \tanh(\alpha \cdot QH)

---

2. Codified Harmony (CH)  
Purpose: Represent structural behavioral alignment with canonical principles.

Type: Vector

Dimensions:

CH = \begin{bmatrix}
H{\text{symmetry}}\\
H{\text{consistency}}\\
H{\text{coherence}}\\
H{\text{parsimony}}\\
H{\text{predictive integrity}}\\
H{\text{ethical invariants}}
\end{bmatrix}

Normalized Magnitude:

CH{\text{norm}} = \frac{|CH|}{\sqrt{6}} \in [0, 1]

---

3. Harmony Coefficient (HC)  
Composite Score:

HC = \beta \cdot QH + (1 - \beta) \cdot CH{\text{norm}}

- Default  \beta = 0.6 

---

4. Harmony Resonance (HR)  
Final emergent measure:

HR = QH \cdot CH{\text{norm}}

- Used in Lattice ‚Üí Bridge Harmony Engine
- Governs:
  - Self-repair
  - Sovereignty checks
  - Drift detection
  - Federation alignment

---

5. Canonical Invariants

Invariant	Description	
Bounded Harmony	0 \leq QH \leq 1	
Constraint Dominance	If  CH = 0 , then  H = 0	
Non-negative Interaction	I{ij} \in [0, 1]	
Weighted State Conservation	\sum w_i = 1	

---

6. Engine Usage

Engine	QH Usage	CH Usage	
Umbra	State convergence	Safe-memory write	
Sovereign	Alignment score	Permission gates	
Lattice	Node coherence	Network-level invariants	
EnvSync	Stable env score	Deployment rules	

---

7. Symbolic Representation
- Œº: Quantified Harmony scalar
- ùåÜ: Harmony Sigil (Bridge Seal)
  - Used in:
    - Stabilization logs
    - Parity confirmations
    - Dominion epochs
    - Vault artifacts

