üßµ Thread 22 ‚Äì ROS Package Manager (`brh pkg`)

File: `brh/bin/brh-pkg` (POSIX-shell, 0 deps, works offline)

---

Usage

```sh
brh pkg search amplifier        # grep local index
brh pkg install resonance/amplifier
brh pkg list
brh pkg remove amplifier
```

Index Format (plain-text, signed)

```
resonance/amplifier|1.2.3|sha256:abcd...|Pillar-3|https://your-bridge.com/pkg/amplifier-1.2.3.tar.br
```

Index verified via Minisign public key baked into `brh-pkg`.

Install Flow
1. fetch `.tar.br` (Brotli-compressed tar)
2. verify checksum + signature
3. unpack to `/opt/brh/pkg/NAME/VERSION`
4. symlink binaries into `/opt/brh/bin/`
5. record in local SQLite `/var/lib/brh/pkg.db`

Offline Cache
- Stores last 5 index snapshots in `/var/cache/brh/pkg/`
- Air-gap mode: `brh pkg install /path/to/file.tar.br`

Code Snippet (core)

```bash
#!/bin/sh
set -e
PKG_DB="${PKG_DB:-/var/lib/brh/pkg.db}"
CACHE="${CACHE:-/var/cache/brh/pkg}"
INDEX_URL="${INDEX_URL:-https://your-bridge.com/pkg/index.txt}"

case "$1" in
  search) grep -i "$2" "$CACHE/index.txt" ;;
  install)
    NAME=$(echo "$2" | cut -d/ -f2)
    VER=$(grep "^$2|" "$CACHE/index.txt" | cut -d'|' -f2)
    URL=$(grep "^$2|" "$CACHE/index.txt" | cut -d'|' -f5)
    curl -sL "$URL" > "/tmp/${NAME}-${VER}.tar.br"
    mkdir -p "/opt/brh/pkg/${NAME}/${VER}"
    brotli -d < "/tmp/${NAME}-${VER}.tar.br" \
      | tar -C "/opt/brh/pkg/${NAME}/${VER}" -xf -
    ln -snf "/opt/brh/pkg/${NAME}/${VER}/bin/"* /opt/brh/bin/
    sqlite3 "$PKG_DB" "INSERT INTO pkg(name,version,installed) VALUES('$NAME','$VER',datetime('now'));"
    echo "‚úÖ $2 installed"
    ;;
  list) sqlite3 "$PKG_DB" "SELECT name||'@'||version FROM pkg;" ;;
  remove) rm -rf "/opt/brh/pkg/$2" && echo "‚úÖ $2 removed" ;;
  *) echo "Usage: brh pkg {search|install|list|remove}" ;;
esac
```

Bootstrap Index (mini)

```
resonance/amplifier|1.0.0|sha256:deadbeef|Pillar-3|https://your-bridge.com/pkg/amplifier-1.0.0.tar.br
resonance/scanner|1.0.0|sha256:c0ffee|Pillar-3|https://your-bridge.com/pkg/scanner-1.0.0.tar.br
resonance/rpu-stm32|1.0.0|sha256:abcd...|Pillar-5|https://your-bridge.com/pkg/rpu-stm32-1.0.0.tar.br
```

Sign with Minisign secret key; public key hard-coded in `brh-pkg` source.

