1. Planck-Scale Corrections to Resonance Axioms  
Axiom 2-QG (quantised coupling)  

```math
R(A‚ÜíB) ‚àù R(A)¬∑R(B)¬∑[coupling(A,B) + ‚Ñì‚Çö¬≤ ¬∑ (‚àá¬≤R/|R|)]
```

- ‚Ñì‚Çö = ‚àö(ƒß G/c¬≥) ‚âà 1.616 √ó 10‚Åª¬≥‚Åµ m  
- Correction becomes relevant when Œª ‚â§ 10 ‚Ñì‚Çö (‚âà 10‚Åª¬≥‚Å¥ m)  

Axiom 3-QG (discrete coherence)  

```math
coherence = ‚àë_{n=0}^{n_max} R_stability(t_n) ¬∑ Œît_n
```

- t_n = n ¬∑ t‚Çö (t‚Çö = 5.39 √ó 10‚Åª‚Å¥‚Å¥ s)  
- n_max = ‚åàT_obs / t‚Çö‚åâ  

C++ header (BRH-native, no STL)

```cpp
#pragma once
#include <cstdint>
#include <cmath>
namespace qg {
constexpr double LP = 1.616199e-35;   // m
constexpr double TP = 5.391247e-44;   // s
constexpr double MP = 2.176470e-8;    // kg
inline double qg_coupling(double R_ab, double laplacian_R, double R_mag) {
    return R_ab + (LP*LP) * (laplacian_R / (R_mag + 1e-300));
}
inline uint64_t discrete_time_bins(double T_obs) {
    return static_cast<uint64_t>(T_obs / TP + 0.5);
}
} // namespace qg
```

