1. Skin Patch Layout ‚Äì `skin_array.py`

```python
import gdspy, numpy as np

lib = gdspy.GdsLibrary()
ly = {'patch': 1, 'feed': 2, 'gnd': 3, 'pass': 9}

Œª = 1.9e3  # ¬µm (60 GHz)
patch_w = patch_l = Œª/2  # 950 ¬µm
pitch = 2.5e3              # ¬µm

skin = lib.new_cell('SkinArray')

for row in range(16):
    for col in range(16):
        x = col * pitch
        y = row * pitch
        # patch
        patch = gdspy.Rectangle((x, y), (x+patch_w, y+patch_l), layer=ly['patch'])
        skin.add(patch)
        # inset feed
        inset = patch_w/3
        feed = gdspy.Rectangle((x+inset, y+patch_l/2-25),
                               (x+inset+50, y+patch_l/2+25), layer=ly['feed'])
        skin.add(feed)

lib.write_gds('skin_array.gds')
```

