1. Ground Grid ‚Äì `schumann_grid.py`

```python
import gdspy, numpy as np

lib = gdspy.GdsLibrary()
ly = {'copper': 1, 'via': 2, 'mast': 3}

# 1 km¬≤ drawn at 1:10 000 ‚Üí 100 mm √ó 100 mm
grid = lib.new_cell('SchumannGrid')

# 10 m mesh wires
pitch = 1_000  # ¬µm (10 m real)
for i in range(101):
    h = gdspy.FlexPath([(i*pitch, 0), (i*pitch, 100_000)], width=50, layer=ly['copper'])
    v = gdspy.FlexPath([(0, i*pitch), (100_000, i*pitch)], width=50, layer=ly['copper'])
    grid.add([h, v])

# 30 m mast (center)
mast = gdspy.Round((50_000, 50_000), 500, layer=ly['mast'])
grid.add(mast)

lib.write_gds('schumann_whisper.gds')
```

